Function Reference/is admin bar showing « WordPress Codex
-----------

This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks if
the WordPress
[Toolbar](/Administration_Screens#Toolbar "Administration Screens") is
being displayed. This is a boolean function, meaning it returns either
TRUE or FALSE.

Usage
-----

` <?php is_admin_bar_showing(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Return Values
-------------

 `(boolean)` 
:   True on success, false on failure.

Examples
--------

    <?php
    if ( is_admin_bar_showing() ) {
        // do something
    }
    ?>

Notes
-----

-   This function will always return true in the WordPress admin.
-   Uses `_get_admin_bar_pref()`.

Change Log
----------

Since: 3.1.0

Source File
-----------

`is_admin_bar_showing()` is located in `wp-includes/admin-bar.php`.

